---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Heading from "../components/Heading.astro";
import BackButton from "../components/BackButton.astro";
import HoySeCome1 from "../components/HoySeCome1.astro";
import HoySeCome2 from "../components/HoySeCome2.astro";
---

<Layout title="App Development">
  <div class="max-w-screen-md m-auto p-4 my-4 antialiased">
    <Heading />
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-extrabold leading-tight text-gray-900 lg:mb-6 lg:text-4xl dark:text-white">
      <span class="text-gradient"
        >App Development</span>
    </h1>
    <br>
    <p class="lead text-white">
      I have some experience with app development, mostly with React Native. Most of them are tests and experiments I made for college projects. 
    </p>
    <br>
    <h1 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-extrabold leading-tight text-gray-900 lg:mb-6 lg:text-4xl dark:text-white">Hoy Se Come</h1>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    <HoySeCome1 />
    <HoySeCome2 />
    </div>
    <p class="lead text-white">
      Hoy Se Come is a mobile app where the user can find recipes depending on the ingredients they have at home. The recipes are searched from the Spoonacular API. This app was made in Android Studio with Java and Kotlin.
    </p>
    <BackButton />
</div>
</Layout>

